# Styling Conventions

## CSS Framework
- Use **Tailwind CSS 4** via `@tailwindcss/vite`
- Import Tailwind in `src/app.css`: `@import 'tailwindcss';`
- Prettier automatically sorts Tailwind classes

## CSS Architecture

### Custom CSS Classes
- Define custom classes in `src/app.css`
- Use semantic class names: `.hero`, `.scoreboard`, `.game-wrapper`
- Use utility classes for common patterns: `.primary`, `.secondary`

### Color Scheme
- Dark theme with light accents
- Use rgba colors for transparency
- Primary color: `#38bdf8` (cyan)
- Secondary color: `#6366f1` (indigo)
- Background: `#0f172a` (slate-900)
- Text: `#e2e8f0` (slate-200)

### Styling Patterns
- Use backdrop-filter for glassmorphism effects
- Use linear gradients for buttons and highlights
- Use border-radius consistently (12px, 16px, 18px, 999px for pills)
- Use box-shadow for depth

### Responsive Design
- Use CSS media queries for mobile breakpoints
- Mobile-first approach when possible
- Max-width: 960px for main content

### Component Classes
- Prefix component-specific classes: `.game-wrapper`, `.result-wrapper`
- Use BEM-like naming for modifiers: `.feedback.correct`, `.feedback.wrong`

## Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Provide alt text for images
- Use proper heading hierarchy
- Ensure sufficient color contrast
